('34737', '2', 'Place ground ham in a bowl, and stir in eggs, mayonnaise, and pickled okra.'),
('34737', '3', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('34737', '4', 'Spread on: rye bread slices.'),
('34738', '1', 'Place tomato slices on paper towels. sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon salt, and let stand 5 minutes.'),
('34738', '2', 'Place tomatoes, zucchini, and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Sprinkle evenly with Creole seasoning and cornstarch. shake to remove excess.'),
('34738', '3', 'Combine breadcrumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and pepper in a shallow bowl.'),
('34738', '4', 'Whisk 3 egg whites in a small bowl until frothy. Dip half of vegetables in egg whites, draining excess. Dredge vegetables, in batches, in breadcrumb mixture. Repeat procedure with remaining egg whites, vegetables, and breadcrumb mixture.'),
('34738', '5', 'Arrange vegetables on wire racks coated with cooking spray. place racks on aluminum foil-lined pans. (Do not overlap vegetables.)'),
('34738', '6', 'Bake at 400 for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.'),
('34738', '7', 'Serve immediately with Horseradish Sauce.'),
('34741', '1', 'Trim tops of okra, being careful not to cut into pods.'),
('34741', '2', 'Cut an X in bottom of each tomato and immerse tomatoes in a 2-quart saucepan of boiling water for 10 seconds.'),
('34741', '3', 'Transfer tomatoes with a slotted spoon (save boiling water) to a bowl of ice and cold water to cool, then peel.'),
('34741', '4', 'Add 1 tablespoon salt to boiling water, then add okra and cook, uncovered, until just tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('34741', '5', 'Drain okra in a colander, then plunge into same ice water to stop cooking.'),
('34741', '6', 'Drain okra and pat dry with paper towels.'),
('34741', '7', 'Quarter tomatoes lengthwise and seed, then cut each quarter lengthwise into 1/2-inch-wide strips.'),
('34741', '8', 'Puree onion, garlic, ginger, jalapeno (to taste), and 1/4 cup chicken broth in a blender.'),
('34741', '9', 'Pat scallops dry and sprinkle with pepper and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('34741', '10', 'Brush a 12-inch nonstick skillet with 1/2 teaspoon oil and heat over moderately high heat until just beginning to smoke. Brown scallops in 2 batches, turning once, about 4 minutes total.'),
('34741', '11', 'Transfer scallops as browned with tongs to a plate and keep warm, covered with foil. (Scallops will not be cooked through.)'),
('34741', '12', 'Add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil to skillet and reduce heat to moderate.'),
('34741', '13', 'Add puree carefully (it may splatter), then add curry powder. Boil, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.'),
('34741', '14', 'Add coconut milk and remaining 3/4 cup broth and bring to a simmer.'),
('34741', '15', 'Add tomato strips and simmer, stirring frequently, until tomatoes are softened, 3 to 4 minutes. Season sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('34741', '16', 'Stir in scallops and okra and simmer until scallops are just cooked through, about 3 minutes. Divide scallops, vegetables, and sauce among 4 plates and sprinkle with cilantro.'),
('34741', '17', 'Each serving contains about 239 calories and 8 grams fat.'),
('34741', '18', 'Self'),
('34744', '1', 'Cook okra as directed on package. set aside.'),
('34744', '2', 'Mix dressing, onions and pepper.'),
('34744', '3', 'Divide greens and tomatoes evenly between six salad plates. sprinkle with okra.'),
('34744', '4', 'Drizzle with dressing mixture.'),
('34746', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('34746', '2', 'Add chicken. cook 3 minutes on each side or until browned.'),
('34746', '3', 'Add pepper stir-fry and next 6 ingredients (through red pepper), stirring to combine.'),
('34746', '4', 'Pour tomatoes over chicken mixture. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes. Uncover. cook 3 minutes.'),
('34746', '5', 'Add parsley and butter, stirring until butter melts.'),
('34749', '1', 'In a large enameled cast-iron casserole, whisk the flour with 1/2 cup of oil until smooth. Cook the roux over moderately low heat, whisking often, until deep brown, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.'),
('34749', '2', 'Add the onion, celery, bell peppers and garlic and cook over moderately low heat, stirring, until the onion is translucent, about 20 minutes.'),
('34749', '3', 'Gradually add the stock to the casserole, whisking until smooth.'),
('34749', '4', 'Add the andouille, bay leaves, jerk paste, thyme and paprika and bring to a simmer. Cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('34749', '5', 'Add the okra to the casserole and simmer until tender, 15 minutes. Stir in the chicken meat and season the gumbo with salt, pepper and Tabasco. Discard the bay leaves, ladle the gumbo over rice, garnish with the scallions and serve with Tabasco.'),
('34751', '1', 'Brown chicken in drippings in a large Dutch oven.'),
('34751', '2', 'Remove chicken, and set aside. Reserve drippings in Dutch oven.'),
('34751', '3', 'Add onion, green pepper, okra, celery, and parsley to Dutch oven. cook over low heat 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Return chicken to Dutch oven.'),
('34751', '4', 'Add water, tomatoes, salt, and pepper, stirring well. Simmer, uncovered, 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.'),
('34751', '5', 'Remove chicken from gumbo. bone and chop meat. Return meat to gumbo, stirring well. Cook until thoroughly heated.'),
('34751', '6', 'Serve gumbo over rice.'),
('34751', '7', 'Add a small amount of fil powder to each serving, if desired.'),
('34752', '1', 'Melt half of the butter in a saute pan (reserving the other 1/4 cup) over medium-high heat, and saute onion until it caramelizes.'),
('34752', '2', 'Add the mushrooms and cook until they become tender and give up their juices. Strain and set aside. In another saucepan whisk together demi-glace, tomato paste, and red wine and simmer over low heat, allowing to reduce and thicken. (Begin okra and steak as directed below.) Just before serving sauce, whisk in the remaining 1/4 cup of cubed butter, and add mushroom-onion mixture. Taste and add salt and pepper, to taste.'),
('34752', '3', 'Heat oil in deep fryer to 375 degrees F, or as instructed in manufacturer''s directions. Shake cornstarch, salt and pepper in a plastic bag and add okra, shaking to coat. Deep-fry until golden brown.'),
('34752', '4', 'Drain on paper towels and re-season with salt and pepper while the oil is still glistening.'),
('34755', '1', 'Place a heavy baking sheet on middle rack of oven, then preheat oven to 400F.'),
('34755', '2', 'Toss squash with 1 teaspoon salt, then drain in a colander 30 minutes. Pat squash dry.'),
('34755', '3', 'Cook scallions (except greens) and garlic in oil with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('34755', '4', 'Add squash and okra and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender, 7 to 9 minutes.'),
('34755', '5', 'Remove from heat and stir in tomatoes.'),
('34755', '6', 'Transfer to a large bowl, then toss with corn, cheese, basil, cornmeal, and scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('34758', '1', 'To prepare sauce, heat a small saucepan over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('34758', '2', 'Add onion and next 5 ingredients (through garlic) to pan. cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broth, sugar, allspice, and tomatoes. Partially cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('34758', '3', 'To prepare coo-coo, place cornmeal and 1 teaspoon salt in a large saucepan. Gradually add 7 cups water, stirring constantly with a whisk. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium, and cook 15 minutes, stirring frequently.'),
('34758', '4', 'Add corn and okra. cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly.'),
('34758', '5', 'Remove from heat.'),
('34758', '6', 'Place butter in a small skillet over medium heat. cook 2 minutes or until browned.'),
('34758', '7', 'Add butter to coo-coo. stir well.'),
('34758', '8', 'Serve sauce over coo-coo.'),
('34761', '1', 'Heat an 8 quart dutch oven or other heavy bottomed pot over medium high heat until very hot. Generously salt and pepper the duck legs then add them to the pot, skin side down.'),
('34761', '2', 'Add the sausage slices around the duck in a single layer and allow to brown. Flip the sausage slices as they brown then flip the duck legs when they no longer stick to the pan.'),
('34761', '3', 'Transfer the sausage to a plate as they finish browning then transfer the duck legs when they are nice and brown on both sides.The pan should now have about 1 tablespoon of fat rendered from the sausages and duck. If there is more, drain the excess off into a ramekin and set aside. To make the mirepoix, add the onions and celery along with a generous pinch of salt and saute until soft and translucent.'),
('34761', '4', 'Add the two bell peppers, garlic and chili pepper of your choice and continue to saute until the onions are starting to caramelize and the bell peppers are nice and soft. Take the pot off the heat and set aside.Now we''re going to make the roux. What we''re doing here is caramelizing the flour until it''s dark chocolate brown. To avoid burning it, it needs constant supervision and stirring which will take anywhere from 30 minutes to an hour. Don''t use a non-stick pan or silicon utensil to stir as they are typically not safe to use at temperatures as high as this mixture will get. I''d recommend using a stainless steel whisk or a flat edged wooden paddle. If you use a wooden paddle, be prepared to have it scorch a little. Lastly be very careful not to splash this on yourself as it''s a guaranteed trip to the ER if you do.'),
('34761', '5', 'Add any reserved fat you have from the duck and sausage to a 1/4 C measuring cup and top off with duck fat, clarified butter, or lard. Do not use regular butter, as the milk solids in it will burn.'),
('34761', '6', 'Add the fat to to a medium sized sauce pan and heat over medium low heat until very hot.'),
('34761', '7', 'Add the flour and immediately start stirring. Be sure you keep every part of the roux moving so it does not burn. As long as it''s not smoking you can turn the heat up in small increments but turn it down if you start to see smoke. As the roux reaches a medium brown color (like beef gravy), turn the heat down a little to slow the process down. You want to get it to the color of dark chocolate (photo above), but there is a very fine line between that and burnt.As soon as it''s reached the desired color, remove the pot from the heat and stir in some of the mirepoix to bring the temperature down quickly. Once it''s cool enough to touch, have a taste. If it tastes bitter, you need to throw it out and start over.'),
('34761', '8', 'Add the roux and chicken stock into the large pot with the rest of the mirepoix.'),
('34761', '9', 'Put the pot over a medium high flame and whisk until the roux is dissolved and the mixture begins to boil.Turn the heat down to maintain a gentle simmer and add the duck, sausage and the rest of the gumbo ingredients. Cover with a lid set slightly ajar to allow steam to escape and simmer until the duck is tender (about 1- 1 1/2 hours).In the meantime, cook the rice, and peel and devein the shrimp.When the duck is tender, remove the legs from the gumbo and allow them to cool enough to handle. Take the meat off the bones and add it back to the pot. Taste for seasonings and add more salt and pepper as needed and adjust the spiciness with cayenne pepper. Turn the heat up and bring the gumbo to a boil then add the shrimp, stirring to submerge. Cover immediately and remove the pot from the heat. The residual heat will gently cook the shrimp to perfection in about 7 minutes (use less time if your shrimp are small).To serve, put a small amount of rice in the bottom of a shallow bowl and top with the gumbo. Sprinkle with parsley and serve with hot sauce and bread.'),
('34762', '1', 'Mix cornmeal and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne in small bowl.'),
('34762', '2', 'Add okra and toss lightly to coat.'),
('34762', '3', 'Pour okra into sieve and shake off excess cornmeal.'),
('34762', '4', 'Heat 4 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),
('34762', '5', 'Add okra and saute until coating is golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer okra to paper towels to drain. sprinkle with salt and pepper. Wipe out skillet.'),
('34762', '6', 'Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet over medium heat.'),
('34762', '7', 'Add corn, squash, and garlic. saute 2 minutes.'),
('34762', '8', 'Add tomatoes. cover and cook until squash is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('34762', '9', 'Mix in okra, cilantro, and green onions.'),
('34762', '10', 'Remove from heat. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and more cayenne, if desired.'),
('34764', '1', 'In a large, heavy pot, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.'),
('34764', '2', 'Add the onions and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 10 minutes.'),
('34764', '3', 'Add the celery, bell pepper, garlic, thyme and crushed pepper. Season with salt and pepper and cook until the vegetables are softened, about 10 minutes.'),
('34764', '4', 'Add the wine and boil over moderately high heat until reduced to a syrup, about 1 minute.'),
('34764', '5', 'Add the tomato juices and bay leaves and boil until reduced by half, about 4 minutes.'),
('34764', '6', 'Add the stock, bring to a boil and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.'),
('34764', '7', 'In a large skillet, melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.'),
('34764', '8', 'Add the okra, season with salt and pepper and cook over moderately high heat, stirring a few times, until browned, about 4 minutes.'),
('34764', '9', 'Add the tomatoes and bring to a boil. Stir the okra and tomatoes into the soup and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes longer. Discard the bay leaves.'),
('34764', '10', 'Add the crabmeat to the soup and simmer until just heated through. Stir in the basil and season with salt, pepper and Tabasco. Ladle the soup into shallow bowls and serve.'),
('34765', '1', 'Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('34765', '2', 'While rice cooks, combine flour and oil in a Dutch oven. saute over medium-high heat 3 minutes.'),
('34765', '3', 'Add onion and next 6 ingredients (onion through red pepper). cook 3 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.'),
('34765', '4', 'Stir in chicken, kielbasa, tomatoes, and broth. cook 6 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('34765', '5', 'Serve over rice.'),
('34766', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('34766', '2', 'Add flour. cook 1 minute or until lightly browned, stirring constantly with a whisk.'),
('34766', '3', 'Add broth. stir with a whisk until thick.'),
('34766', '4', 'Pour into a bowl. set aside. Wipe pan clean with paper towels.'),
('34766', '5', 'Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in pan over medium heat.'),
('34766', '6', 'Add onion and ham. cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('34766', '7', 'Add bell pepper and next 4 ingredients (through okra). cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('34766', '8', 'Add broth mixture, water, and next 6 ingredients (through tomatoes). Bring to a boil. reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in shrimp. cook 4 minutes or until shrimp are done. Sprinkle with parsley.'),
('34767', '1', 'Prepare Dinner in large saucepan as directed on package.'),
('34767', '2', 'Meanwhile, cook and stir green peppers and okra in nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray until crisp-tender.'),
('34767', '3', 'Add green pepper mixture to prepared Dinner along with the shrimp, tomatoes and hot pepper sauce. mix lightly.  Cook on medium heat until heated through, stirring occasionally.'),
('34769', '1', 'In a soup pot, combine the chicken, onions, 2 tablespoons of the garlic, the yellow squash, okra, chicken broth, diced tomatoes, tomato paste, and bay leaves. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Lower the heat and simmer for 30 minutes, until the vegetables are very tender.'),
('34769', '2', 'Remove the bay leaves. Set aside.'),
('34769', '3', 'Just before serving, reheat the soup, then warm the oil in a large skillet and saut the green bell pepper, remaining garlic, basil, and shrimp until the shrimp are just pink.'),
('34769', '4', 'Add the hot chili sauce, the lemon juice, salt, and the contents of the skillet to the hot soup.'),
('34771', '1', 'Stir together flour and oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, for about 10 minutes or until mixture turns reddish brown. Spoon mixture into a slow cooker. stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice. Cover and cook on high setting for one hour. then 5 hours on low setting. Twenty minutes before serving, add shrimp to slow cooker. mix well. Cover and cook on low setting. Ladle gumbo over cooked rice in soup bowls.'),
('34774', '1', 'Heat a large saute pan over medium heat and add the chorizo. Cook the sausage until cooked through and crispy.'),
('34774', '2', 'Remove the sausage from the pan, leaving the fat in the pan.'),
('34774', '3', 'Add the peanut oil to the chorizo fat and add the cumin seeds and mustard seeds. Cook''s Note: Be careful! The seeds will start popping. When the seeds start to pop, add the curry leaves, which will sputter too, so watch out! Then add the onion, peanuts, garlic, turmeric, and paprika, sauteing until the onions are soft and golden brown.'),
('34774', '4', 'Add the tomatoes and okra. Cook until the tomatoes are soft and mushy and the okra is tender.'),
('34774', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a small nonstick pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium heat and scramble the eggs.'),
('34774', '6', 'Add the cooked rice to the tomato mixture and stir. Cook until the rice is warmed through. Stir in the chorizo, scrambled eggs, chopped cilantro, and lime juice. Taste the mixture and season with salt, and pepper, to taste.'),
('34776', '1', 'In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat.'),
('34776', '2', 'Add bacon, butter, onion, green pepper and garlic.'),
('34776', '3', 'Saute until the vegetables are soft and the onions are translucent.'),
('34776', '4', 'Add seasoned salt, garlic powder, tomatoes, water, chicken base and okra. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and let simmer for 30 minutes stirring occasionally. Season, to taste, with salt and pepper.'),
